post.description: Use this service to create Split-payments referentes for Multibanco or MB WAY payment requests.

alias.description: Param used only on MB WAY requests. It must be used to define to which phone number the request must be sent.

post.description: Use this request to create Debit Direct Authorizations. This request will create an Authorization PDF with a reference number (authorizationId) , which will be sent to the debtor's email.

adminCallback.description: Use this optional field to receive a communication when this reference is paid.

zipCode.description: zipCode of the address (do not insert the city)

email.description: Debtor's Email. Used to send the Authorization PDF and next payment notifications.

autoProcess.description: Defines if the debit will processed by the API automatically (1) or there will be a manual debit instruction (0).

collectionDay.description: Mandatory if it is defined a periodicity and it's type is RCUR.

periodicity.description: Defines the periodicity of the debit

limitDate.description: Date (YYYY-MM-DD) defined to be the last debit for this Authorization

type.description: Type of debit. OOFF must be used on Authorizations that will only have one debit. RCUR is used for Authorizations that have recurring debits

post.description: Creates an url to a secure form where the customer may finish the Credit Card recurrency. Supports 3D Secure Technology.

autoProcess.description: Parameter that defines the intention of auto-processing payments with a value of 0 for "no" or 1 for "yes."

collectionDay.description: Parameter referring to the transaction execution day in auto-processed payments (Relevant only when autoProcess is set to 1). If left blank, it will assume the current day as reference.

periodicity.description: Paramenter referring to the periodicity of auto-processing (Required if autoProcess = 1)

date.description: In YYYY-MM-DD format. Date from which recurrence activation and use will be possible

limitDate.description: In YYYY-MM-DD format. Date until which the recurrence can be used (After this date, the recurrence expires, and a new one must be executed).

customer.description: Object that encompasses the customer's phone, email and name responsible for the credit card.

notify.description: To define if the customer will be notified with the data of subscription request by email/sms.

phone.description: National mobile phone number for recurrence notifications, one-time payments, and subscriptions (No area code required, enter only 9 digits).

email.description: Email for recurrence notifications, one-time payments, and subscriptions.

name.description: Name of the customer to be displayed in recurrence notifications, one-time payments, and subscriptions.

minutesFormUp.description: Number of minutes that the url for the payment form will remain active. After that time the form will be unaccessible and the reference expired. Max and default 1440 minutes
